<s> As mentioned in the previous messages, there are differences between implementations regarding the HTMLFormElement.submit method.  </s>
<s> In Spyglass Device Mosaic 3, the invocation of the submit() method causes the firing of the ONSUBMIT event prior to performing its intended semantics, and, if the event returns a value that is equivalent (coercable) to FALSE, then those intended semantics (form submission) are ignored.  </s>
<s> We cannot change this implementation even if NS and IE are consistent on this issue, therefore we reiterate our position: you cannot rely on having an event when invoking the submit() method.  </s>
